Metasoma. First tergite 0.7 times as long as apically wide, smooth and with distinct elliptical depression medially (Fig. 557); 
second-sixth
tergites densely and coarsely reticulate-punctate (Fig. 557); sternites densely and coarsely punctate; second sternite distinctly convex, without medio-apical protuberance (Fig. 559); third sternite about 0.3 times as long as second sternite, with medio-apical protuberance triangularly protruding (Fig. 559); hypopygium triangular in ventral view (Fig. 559).
